I beg to move, in page 100, line 29, at the end, to insert: 1 Nottingham, Central:
(i) The following wards of the county borough of Nottingham, namely, Forest, Market, Robin Hood, St. Mary's and Sherwood;
(ii) The rural district of Nottingham" This Amendment arranges for an extra seat for the City of Nottingham.

I beg to move, in page 101, column 2, to leave out line 10, and to insert:
"(i) All wards of the county borough of Oxford east of the River Cherwell;
(ii) all wards of the county borough of Oxford west of the River Cherwell." As my hon. Friend the Member for Oxford (Mr. Hogg) cannot be here, I think it is only right that I should move this Amendment which stands in his name, and, although it is not possible for me to put it with all the skill which his legal knowledge would give him, I feel sure the Home Secretary will grant what seems to be an improvement on the present position.
